Sentencas: Vanadium-doped strontium molybdate (SVM) has been investigated as a potential anode material for solid oxide fuel cells due to its high electronic conductivity of about 1000 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C in reducing atmospheres.
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In this work, NiO is introduced to SVM with the B-site excess design to induce in situ growth of Ni nanoparticles in the anodic operational conditions.
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Ni particles are exsolved from the parent oxide phase as clearly demonstrated with various techniques including X-ray diffraction, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy, scanning electron microscopy, and transmission electron microscopy.
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The exsolved Ni nanoparticles significantly boost the electrocatalytic activity toward fuel oxidation reaction, improving the peak power density by 160% from 0.21 to 0.56 W cm(-2) at 800 degrees C when using H-2 as the fuel, meanwhile reducing the total interfacial polarization resistance by 56% from 0.81 to 0.36 Omega cm(2).
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The Ni-exsolved SVM anode also shows excellent catalytic activity toward H2S-containing and hydrocarbon fuels, providing peak power densities of 0.43, 0.36, and 0.22 W cm -2 at 800 degrees C for H-2-50 ppm H2S, syngas, and ethanol, respectively.
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In addition, the cell with the Ni-exsolved SVM anode presents a stable power output, indicating that the Ni-SVM is a potential SOFC anode electrocatalyst for various fuels.
Titulo: Vanadium-Doped Strontium Molybdate with Exsolved Ni Nanoparticles as Anode Material for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
